---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout title="Home">
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>rust-zkp</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      A learning project that builds a minimal ZK-Rollup from scratch in Rust —
      no SNARK frameworks, just the cryptographic primitives composed by hand.
    </p>
    <div class="cta">
      <a href={`${base}/notes/`} class="btn primary">Read the notes</a>
      <a href={`${base}/demos/`} class="btn">Try the playground</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="features">
    <h2>What's inside</h2>
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>ZKP primitives</h3>
        <p>Pedersen commitment, Sigma protocol, Fiat-Shamir, Merkle membership, range proofs.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Mini rollup</h3>
        <p>Account state, signed transactions with replay protection, atomic batch processing.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Backend stack</h3>
        <p>HTTP API server (axum), CLI client (clap), persistent storage (sled), CI/CD.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>WASM playground</h3>
        <p>Try the cryptographic primitives in your browser — running real Rust code via WebAssembly.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="features">
    <h2>Approach</h2>
    <p>
      Most ZKP tutorials either show toy code or jump straight to SNARK frameworks.
      This project deliberately sits in the middle: build every primitive yourself,
      compose them into a working system, and understand why each piece exists.
    </p>
    <p>
      The cryptography is intentionally simplified (small primes instead of elliptic curves,
      direct verification instead of SNARKs) to keep the focus on architecture and
      protocol design. See <a href={`${base}/notes/mini_rollup`}>this note</a> for what's
      production-grade and what's not.
    </p>
  </section>

  <style>
    .hero {
      padding: 32px 0 48px;
    }
    .hero h1 {
      font-size: 3rem;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
      font-family: ui-monospace, "SF Mono", Menlo, monospace;
    }
    .lead {
      font-size: 1.15rem;
      color: var(--fg-muted);
      max-width: 640px;
    }
    .cta {
      margin-top: 24px;
      display: flex;
      gap: 12px;
    }
    .btn {
      display: inline-block;
      padding: 10px 18px;
      border-radius: 6px;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      background: white;
      color: var(--fg);
      text-decoration: none;
      font-weight: 500;
    }
    .btn:hover { border-color: var(--accent); color: var(--accent); }
    .btn.primary {
      background: var(--accent);
      color: white;
      border-color: var(--accent);
    }
    .btn.primary:hover { color: white; opacity: 0.9; }
    .features {
      margin-top: 48px;
    }
    .grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
      gap: 16px;
      margin-top: 16px;
    }
    .card {
      padding: 20px;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 8px;
      background: white;
    }
    .card h3 {
      margin: 0 0 8px;
      font-size: 1.05rem;
    }
    .card p {
      margin: 0;
      color: var(--fg-muted);
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
